# AC Mitsubishi – HA Integration Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Python 3.12, asyncio, Home Assistant core API
- Protocol: Modbus RTU over raw TCP (see modbus.py)
- No third-party Modbus library — custom implementation in modbus.py

## Architecture – file roles (never blur these)
- `const.py`       — register maps, mode dicts, limits ONLY. Zero logic, zero HA imports.
- `modbus.py`      — raw TCP framing + CRC only. Zero HA imports. Must be independently testable.
- `coordinator.py` — polling via DataUpdateCoordinator + write helpers. Owns the ACState dataclass.
- `climate.py`     — ClimateEntity state properties + async service handlers. No direct Modbus calls.
- `config_flow.py` — UI setup only. Connectivity test via ModbusRTUClient context manager.
- `__init__.py`    — async_setup_entry / async_unload_entry only.

## HA conventions — always follow
- Use `DataUpdateCoordinator` for ALL polling; never poll inside an entity.
- Entities MUST inherit `CoordinatorEntity`.
- Never call `schedule_update_ha_state()` — use `async_write_ha_state()`.
- Config entries ONLY — no YAML/configuration.yaml setup.
- All I/O must be async. Never use blocking calls (socket, time.sleep) in the event loop.
- Use `UpdateFailed` (not exceptions) to signal coordinator poll failure.
- Device info must be set via `_attr_device_info` dict on the entity.

## Modbus register map (do not change without updating const.py)
| Register | FC   | Address | Description              |
|----------|------|---------|--------------------------|
| Mode     | 0x03 | 0x0000  | HVAC operating mode      |
| Setpoint | 0x03 | 0x0001  | Target temp × 10 (°C)    |
| Fan      | 0x03 | 0x0002  | Fan speed                |
| Vane     | 0x03 | 0x0003  | Vane/swing position      |
| Power    | 0x03 | 0x0007  | 0=off, 1=on              |
| RoomTemp | 0x04 | 0x0000  | Current temp × 10 (°C)   |

## Testing conventions
- Mock at the `ModbusRTUClient` level, not at the socket level.
- Use `pytest-asyncio` with `asyncio_mode = "auto"`.
- Each test file maps 1-to-1 with a source file (test_modbus.py → modbus.py).
- Coordinator tests use `async_fire_time_changed` from `homeassistant.util.dt`.

## Git branch naming
- `feat/<short-description>` — new functionality
- `fix/<short-description>`  — bug fixes
- `refactor/<short-description>` — internal changes, no behaviour change
- `test/<short-description>` — tests only
